="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em"><path d="M305.913 197.085c0 2.266-1.133 4.815-2.833 6.514L171.087 335.593c-1.7 1.7-4.249 2.832-6.515 2.832s-4.815-1.133-6.515-2.832L26.064 203.599c-1.7-1.7-2.832-4.248-2.832-6.514s1.132-4.816 2.832-6.515l14.162-14.163c1.7-1.699 3.966-2.832 6.515-2.832 2.266 0 4.815 1.133 6.515 2.832l111.316 111.317 111.316-111.317c1.7-1.699 4.249-2.832 6.515-2.832s4.815 1.133 6.515 2.832l14.162 14.163c1.7 1.7 2.833 4.249 2.833 6.515z" /></svg></span></span></a><ul class="sub-menu"><li class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-30"><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/contact-us/">Contact Us</a></li></ul></li><li class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-privacy-policy menu-item-29"><a rel="privacy-policy" href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/privacy-policy/">Privacy &#038; Cookie Policy</a></li></ul></div><div class="menu-bar-items"><span class="menu-bar-item search-item"><a aria-label="Open Search Bar" href="#"><span class="gp-icon icon-search"><svg viewBox="0 0 512 512" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M208 48c-88.366 0-160 71.634-160 160s71.634 160 160 160 160-71.634 160-160S296.366 48 208 48zM0 208C0 93.125 93.125 0 208 0s208 93.125 208 208c0 48.741-16.765 93.566-44.843 129.024l133.826 134.018c9.366 9.379 9.355 24.575-.025 33.941-9.379 9.366-24.575 9.355-33.941-.025L337.238 370.987C301.747 399.167 256.839 416 208 416 93.125 416 0 322.875 0 208z" /></svg><svg viewBox="0 0 512 512" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em"><path d="M71.029 71.029c9.373-9.372 24.569-9.372 33.942 0L256 222.059l151.029-151.03c9.373-9.372 24.569-9.372 33.942 0 9.372 9.373 9.372 24.569 0 33.942L289.941 256l151.03 151.029c9.372 9.373 9.372 24.569 0 33.942-9.373 9.372-24.569 9.372-33.942 0L256 289.941l-151.029 151.03c-9.373 9.372-24.569 9.372-33.942 0-9.372-9.373-9.372-24.569 0-33.942L222.059 256 71.029 104.971c-9.372-9.373-9.372-24.569 0-33.942z" /></svg></span></a></span></div></div></nav><div class="site grid-container container hfeed" id="page"><div class="site-content" id="content"><div class="content-area" id="primary"><main class="site-main" id="main"><article id="post-9050" class="post-9050 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-beginner category-food category-italian-word-of-the-day category-meals category-nouns category-time tag-breakfast tag-colazione mv-content-wrapper" itemtype="https://schema.org/CreativeWork" itemscope><div class="inside-article"><header class="entry-header"><h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline">Italian Word of the Day: Colazione (breakfast)</h1><div class="entry-meta"> <span class="posted-on"><time class="updated" datetime="2023-06-28T18:37:52+01:00" itemprop="dateModified">June 28, 2023</time><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2020-07-02T06:00:00+01:00" itemprop="datePublished">July 2, 2020</time></span> <span class="byline">by <span class="author vcard" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" itemscope><a class="url fn n" href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/author/heather-broster/" title="View all posts by Heather Broster" rel="author" itemprop="url"><span class="author-name" itemprop="name">Heather Broster</span></a></span></span></div></header><div class="entry-content" itemprop="text"><p>The word for <em>breakfast</em> in Italian is <em><strong><span class="has-inline-color has-italian-green-color">colazione</span></strong></em> (feminine, plural: <em><strong>colazioni</strong></em>).</p><figure class="wp-block-audio"><audio controls src="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/colazione.m4a"></audio><figcaption><strong>/co·la·zió·ne/</strong></figcaption></figure><div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="778" height="778" src="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/03-colazione-778x778.jpg" alt="italian word for breakfast" class="wp-image-35988" srcset="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/03-colazione-778x778.jpg 778w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/03-colazione-300x300.jpg 300w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/03-colazione-150x150.jpg 150w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/03-colazione-768x768.jpg 768w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/03-colazione-96x96.jpg 96w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/03-colazione.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 778px) 100vw, 778px" /></figure></div><p>Traditionally, the first meal eaten just after waking up was referred to as <em><strong>la prima</strong></em> <em><strong>colazione</strong></em> (<em>the first breakfast</em>), whereas the midday meal was called <em><strong>la seconda colazione</strong></em> (<em>the second breakfast</em>). The latter has since been replaced by the word <em><strong>pranzo</strong></em> (<em>lunch</em>) but the term <em><strong>prima colazione</strong></em> still survives today.</p><div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"><p class="has-text-align-center has-contrast-3-color has-text-color has-medium-font-size"><strong><em>Non bisogna saltare la colazione perché è il pasto più importante della giornata.</em></strong></p><p class="has-text-align-center has-base-color has-text-color"><em>We shouldn&#8217;t skip breakfast because it is the most important meal of the day.</em></p><figure class="wp-block-audio"><audio controls src="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/colazione-frase-1.m4a"></audio></figure></div></div><hr class="wp-block-separator has-css-opacity is-style-dots"/><p>The Italian term comes from the ancient French word <em>collatiòn</em>, which in turn derives from the low Latin <em>collatiònem</em> meaning <em>to contribute</em> <em>/</em> <em>bring together</em>. It is said that term was originally used to describe the meal that the Christian monks of the 4th century took after their evening meeting. (Source: <a href="http://www.treccani.it/vocabolario/colazione/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Treccani</a>)</p><div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="720" height="481" src="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1-720x481.jpg" alt="woman eating breakfast in bed" class="wp-image-9061" srcset="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1-720x481.jpg 720w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /></noscript><img decoding="async" width="720" height="481" src='data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20720%20481%22%3E%3C/svg%3E' data-src="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1-720x481.jpg" alt="woman eating breakfast in bed" class="lazyload wp-image-9061" data-srcset="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1-720x481.jpg 720w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-for-breakfast-1.jpg 800w" data-sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /><figcaption><em><strong>La colazione è il mio pasto preferito.</strong> = Breakfast is my favourite meal.</em></figcaption></figure></div><p>A traditional Italian breakfast for an adult normally consists of <em>hot milk with coffee</em> (<em><strong>caffè latte</strong></em>), a simple <em>coffee</em> (<em><strong>caffè</strong></em>) or <em>tea</em> (<em><strong>tè</strong></em>) along with bread (<strong><em><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/italian-word-of-the-day-pane-bread/">pane</a></em></strong>), butter (<em><strong>burro</strong></em>), jam (<em><strong>marmellata</strong></em>), <em>rusk</em> (<em><strong>fette biscottate</strong></em>), <em>milk buns</em> (<em><strong>panini al latte</strong></em>) and <em>biscuits</em> (<em><strong><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/italian-word-for-cookie-biscotto-day-20/">biscotti</a></strong></em>).</p><p>Children often drink <em>warm milk</em> (<em><strong><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/italian-word-for-milk-latte/">latte</a> caldo</strong></em>) that may contain either <em>barley coffee</em> (<em><strong>caffè d&#8217;orzo</strong></em>) or <em>chocolate</em> (<em><strong><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/italian-word-for-chocolate-cioccolato/">cioccolata</a></strong></em>). Yogurt, <em>fruit juices</em> (<em><strong><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/italian-word-for-juice-succo/">succhi</a> di frutta</strong></em>), <em>honey</em> (<strong><em>miele</em></strong>) and <em>cereal</em> (<em><strong>cereali</strong></em>) are also popular choices these days.</p><p>Those who go to <em>cafés</em> (<em><strong>bar</strong></em>) for breakfast will tend to choose a <strong><em>cappuccino</em></strong> or <em><strong>espresso</strong></em> accompanied by a <em>croissant</em> (<em><strong>cornetto</strong></em>) or other type of <em>pastry</em> (<strong><em>pasticcino</em></strong>).</p><div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"><p class="has-text-align-center has-contrast-3-color has-text-color has-medium-font-size"><em><strong>Hai già mangiato? No? Allora andiamo a fare colazione al bar.</strong></em></p><p class="has-text-align-center has-base-color has-text-color"><em>Have you eaten already? No? Then let&#8217;s go have breakfast at the café.</em></p><figure class="wp-block-audio"><audio controls src="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/colazione-frase-2.m4a"></audio></figure></div></div><hr class="wp-block-separator has-css-opacity is-style-dots"/><div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="720" height="459" src="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1-720x459.jpg" alt="cup of coffee and croissant on a bar table" class="wp-image-9059" srcset="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1-720x459.jpg 720w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1-300x191.jpg 300w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1-768x490.jpg 768w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /></noscript><img decoding="async" width="720" height="459" src='data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20720%20459%22%3E%3C/svg%3E' data-src="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1-720x459.jpg" alt="cup of coffee and croissant on a bar table" class="lazyload wp-image-9059" data-srcset="https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1-720x459.jpg 720w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1-300x191.jpg 300w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1-768x490.jpg 768w, https://dailyitalianwords.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/italian-word-for-breakfast-colazione-1.jpg 800w" data-sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /><figcaption><strong><em>Mi piace bere il caffè a colazione.</em></strong> = <em>I like drinking coffee at breakfast.</em></figcaption></figure></div><p>Some other phrases containing the word <em><strong>colazione</strong></em> describe different types of breakfast:</p><ul><li><strong><em>colazione all’inglese</em></strong> = English breakfast</li><li><strong><em>colazione alla forchetta / in forchetta</em></strong> = breakfast with solid food, warm or cold, that requires the use of a knife and fork</li><li><strong><em>colazione al sacco</em></strong> = packed breakfast to take on a walk or class trip, you can also say <em><strong>pranzo</strong></em> (<em>lunch</em>) or <em><strong>merenda al sacco</strong></em> (<em>snack</em>)</li><li><strong><em>colazione di lavoro</em></strong> = a quick lunch with colleagues where you discuss business while eating</li></ul><p>Following <em>breakfast</em> is <em>lunch</em> (<em><strong><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/italian-word-for-lunch-pranzo/">pranzo</a></strong></em>), which is regarded as the most important meal of the day. Most businesses allow their employees a <em>lunch</em> <em>break</em> (<em><strong>pausa pranzo</strong></em>) which lasts from 1 p.m. to 3 p.m. After school, many children and adults enjoy a mid-afternoon snack called <em><strong><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/italian-word-merenda-afternoon-snack/">merenda</a></strong></em>. The day ends with <em>supper</em> (<em><strong><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/italian-word-for-dinner-cena/">cena</a></strong></em>) during which a <em><strong>primo</strong></em> (<em>first course</em>) and <strong><em>secondo</em></strong> (<em>second course</em>) are usually served. In contrast to Anglosaxon countries where supper is consumed quite early in the evening, Italians tend to eat between 7 p.m. and 9 p.m.</p><div class="saboxplugin-wrap" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person" itemscope itemprop="author"><div class="saboxplugin-tab"><div class="saboxplugin-gravatar"><noscript><img alt='Heather Broster' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b1caf76d8fa0a8b8361effb65fc7f7ac?s=100&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b1caf76d8fa0a8b8361effb65fc7f7ac?s=200&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-100 photo' height='100' width='100' itemprop="image"/></noscript><img alt='Heather Broster' src='data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20100%20100%22%3E%3C/svg%3E' data-src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b1caf76d8fa0a8b8361effb65fc7f7ac?s=100&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' data-srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b1caf76d8fa0a8b8361effb65fc7f7ac?s=200&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='lazyload avatar avatar-100 photo' height='100' width='100' itemprop="image"/></div><div class="saboxplugin-authorname"><a href="https://dailyitalianwords.com/author/heather-broster/" class="vcard author" rel="author"><span class="fn">Heather Broster</span></a></div><div class="saboxplugin-desc"><div itemprop="description"><p>Heather Broster is a graduate with honours in linguistics from the University of Western Ontario. She is an aspiring polyglot, proficient in English and Italian, as well as Japanese, Welsh, and French to varying degrees of fluency. Originally from Toronto, Heather has resided in various countries, notably Italy for a period of six years. Her primary focus lies in the fields of language acquisition, education, and bilingual instruction.</p></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div></div></div></div><footer class="entry-meta" aria-label="Entry meta"> <span class="cat-links"><span class="gp-icon icon-categories"><svg viewBox="0 0 512 512" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1em" height="1em"><path d="M0 112c0-26.51 21.49-48 48-48h110.014a48 48 0 0143.592 27.907l12.349 26.791A16 16 0 00